        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 3:56PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 356 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Prestonville, or over Sandy Ridge, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mayodan...
Madison...
Sandy Ridge...
Pine Hall...
Dillard...
Ellisboro...
and Prestonville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
